Ask HN: Would you switch from full time to part time if you could?
text:
You'd have to take a 50% pay cut for going from ~40 hrs/wk to ~20 hrs/wk, and you can discuss whether you would need to be able to keep your health benefits or not, etc.

I think there are plenty of pluses and minuses on various levels, but I'm mostly curious if _you_ would do this right now, if you were benevolent dictator of your own life, and someone asks this question to you today, and you have 24 hours to make a decision.

Thanks.

title: Ask HN: Are TestOut.com's CompTIA prep courses like Network and PC Pro adequate?
text: After 10 years of personal tinkering and customer service jobs that, while have not been bad I have also not enjoyed all that much, I have decided to pursue some technical certifications, starting with CompTIA's A+ and Network+ to switch my career track to the IT sector. I have access to TestOut.com and their prep courses. I understand they are partnered with (possibly owned by) CompTIA and I wanted to see if anyone had used them before to get their respective certifications and if their material was sufficient.

Show HN: SpeakGPT – Voice chats with AI on topics from Twitter to learn English
text:
Hi!

I made a web app to practice English at advanced levels by having 2-way voice conversations with AI. But topics are taken from your Twitter followings section.

Why I made this app? It's not hard to read documentations, or listen a podcast. But how about convince native speaker to change his mind in a discussion? Or jump into a group conversation and tell a story? This last mile of learning language is a pain. And it's my personal problem.

Why Twitter? Twitter feed is a source of hot advanced topics in short form. And it is already customized to your specific interests.

Such conversations give much more fun and benefits than discussing again and again boring general topics like "sports" or "movies". So the time spent on practice not feel wasted.

Demo: https://www.loom.com/share/27e56e949449443194a387bffb3434f9

App: https://www.speakgpt.club/

title: Is ChatGPT the next big bootstrapper opportunity?
Looking for people for cust dev of a start up for running
text:
Hi! We are doing a startup related to running analytics. By analyzing your training data, we can give recommendations on what should have been improved during the latest workout. We also offer a plan for the next workout based on current fatigue and physical fitness.

We are testing the algorithm and you can help us. If you track your speed and heart rate, then we can analyze your and give recommendations. In return for your feedback, of course

If you don't have any data or you aren't willing to share it but this topic is of interest to you please contact us too. It can be really useful to learn your perspective.

Contact me for details

Ask HN: Slack macOS app battery impact
text:
Hey HN! I have a work-issued 2021 14in Macbook Pro and if Slack is open, my battery life is ~half (3-4 hours) of what it is if it's closed. Slack (version 4.31.155) consistently has 2x the "energy impact" of Chrome (loaded up with tabs) in the macOS Activity Monitor.

Hardware acceleration is enabled in Slack settings, and I'm logged into several workspaces as part of our Slack Enterprise Grid setup ( it's moderately annoying that I can't sign out of individual ones I don't care about). But the impact of just having Slack open seems immense. Am I missing something here? Has anyone else seen this behavior over the last few months? Help me save my battery-life!
